<TReshetiloff(-at-)cambridgeassociates.com> wrote:
> 
> There was a post earlier today in which a person
> described lowering the
> engine some and removing the tank that way. I guess
> if you have FI you
> could do it but honestly pulling the motor is not
> that big of a deal. On my
> 78' I leave the trans bolted to the motor and just
> pop the front trans
> mount, mustache bar, and rear trans hangers, a few
> wires, clutch and accel
> cable, and a fuel line and carefully lower the whole
> shebang on a floor
> jack. Install is much easier this way as you dont
> have to wiggle and push
> to get the input shaft into the tranny...
>      I bet there are othe rthings you would love to
> take care of while that
> motor is out anyway. Easily done in a weekend.
> 
